text:
You mentioning the memory you were hit with reminds me of something that happened back in 2012... and it still leaves me uncertain to this day.

My dad and I were vacationing in Japan and one day shortly into the trip were walking down a suburb trying to find a museum in the area.

As we reached an intersection, I was hit with a clear memory of myself being really young, probably around 4-8 years old, running through that intersection and feeling very happy.

There's just one little problem with the memory: I never left my home country of Australia once until that year, 2012.

I was born and raised in Australia, with 2012 being the very first time I ever left the country.

So... how can I have a memory of myself as a child running through that intersection in Japan when I was never there as a child?

To this day, beyond the idea of a past life or some ghost sharing their memories with me, I have no idea where that memory came from
author: @autumbreeze1129
